snippet.textDisplay: My story is literally just like yours with my second baby. She was born back in August and she was always measuring “big” when I went in at 38 weeks to get checked because I was having just back pain! They measured her and they said was 9 lbs and that I should get a c section I said no started walking around the hospital. I got to 9 cm and she came in and was like you really should get the epidural because she’s so big and she might get stuck. I ended up saying yes they came in gave me the epidural at 9 cm 5 min later I started pushing because I just felt her coming down. I was obviously disappointed they kinda made me get the epidural but I also understand doctors just want to be safe. I was in labour for 12 hours which was great with my first I had an induction got the epidural right away and just layed there lol so I’m a big believer of just keep walking. snippet.textDisplay:
During my first pregnancy since it was my first I got really nervous and anxious when it came down to labor. My water actually broke and I went to the hospital, but I wasn't really getting contractions and they induced me. After the induced me I still didn't get them, so the medicine didn't have any affect on me so we just had to wait and they were getting a little worried since the baby can only be inside for so long since my water had already broke. When I did get my contractions and the baby was coming that's when it hit me with the pain and the anxiety so I wasn't listening to the drs and pushed way too much so I ended up having stitches - a lot of stitches lol. My baby was 7 lbs 19 oz or so.

My second baby was the big one, he was 8 lbs 16 oz or so. I did get the IV pain medicine because when I was in the hospital with him I ended up getting a fever. My contractions were really hitting (not like my first) and my husband at that time wasn't there, it was just my mom. So I believe all the emotions and the fever caused me to get desperate, but thankfully I had great nurses that helped me calm down. I did push (not crazy like my first) when I got my contractions during the IV medicine and that really helped me open up. He was a chunky big baby but he's healthy and everything turned out good. I did get a few stitches since he was a little big, but not as bad as my first.

So all in all both were totally different and I know you and Alex will make the best decision for you and Baby Gael. Si Dios quiere we will see Baby G in your next video 💜💜🥰 much love!
